[Link](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1yQ5-cvyv-r8xk93e2i9VHHVybuJvTnOe4ELaf-Lw9FM/)

The mayor of Riverton, Jacky Chan, is 35 years old. Last  night, he was charged with hitting and running over an animal by the town sheriff. A killed calf was found on Arlington Drive at around 10:00 p.m. Emily Parker, a young witness, saw the car hit the calf but didn't see the driver. She recognized the bull horns on the mayor's car.

{% audioPlayer "/audio/the-mayor-kills-a-cat_0.mp3" %}


Emily said, "Yes, that's the mayor's car because it has bull horns on the hood. I know this is his car." The sheriff went to the mayor's house and found him washing a 1972 Cadillac. The mayor explained that he washes his car late at night to avoid the hot sun drying it too fast.

{% audioPlayer "/audio/the-mayor-kills-a-cat_1.mp3" %}


The sheriff noticed one of the bull horns was broken. He asked when it happened, but the mayor didn't know. Later, the sheriff showed the mayor a piece and said it might be the missing part from the horn. The mayor placed it back on the horn and it fit perfectly.

{% audioPlayer "/audio/the-mayor-kills-a-cat_2.mp3" %}


However, the sheriff explained that the piece came from the calf's horn near where they found the killed calf earlier. The mayor was surprised and said he had no idea. He thought he hit a speed bump.

{% audioPlayer "/audio/the-mayor-kills-a-cat_3.mp3" %}

The mayor said, "Let's go to court because I didn't do this." He then suggested getting the calf to Lester’s butcher shop for a barbecue tomorrow at city hall. He wanted to invite Farmer Brown too.

{% audioPlayer "/audio/the-mayor-kills-a-cat_4.mp3" %}

{% audioPlayer "/audio/the-mayor-kills-a-cat_4.mp3" %}

Charged - 被控告
The mayor was charged with hitting and running over an animal.

Sheriff - 警長
A town sheriff charged the mayor.

Killed - 被殺死的
A killed calf was found on Arlington Drive.

Horn - 角
The car had bull horns on the hood.

The mayor's horns are neonized, so they have a soft purple glow at night.

Barbecue - BBQ烤肉
We'll have a big barbecue tomorrow at city hall.

